on in the planetesimal's mantle. This\nstage is characterized by high viscous shear stress that tends to erode\npreviously formed crystal deposits. However, the time scale of this erosion\nprocess is larger that the lifetime of the planetesimal. Hence solid-state\nevolution can be described by a well mixed mantle embedded by a metastable\ncrust and a preserved cumulate at its base.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 2 Aug 2021 15:49:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-03"}
